SIMPLE: pointer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pointer
<hw>Point"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that which, points.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The hand of a timepiece.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a breed of dogs trained to stop at scent of game, and with the nose point it out to sportsmen.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The two stars (Merak and Dubhe) in the Great Bear, the line between which points nearly in the direction of the north star.</def> See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Ursa Major</er>. <sd>(b)</sd> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Diagonal braces sometimes fixed across the hold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pointing</ent>⟦br⟧
